{
  "number": 4135,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/4135",
  "title": "Ability to preselect min and max SELECTED values on rangeSlider, not to be confused with the rangeSlider min and max values",
  "body": "There seems to be a simple way to preselect values on a refinement list like so:\r\n\r\n`const search = instantsearch({\r\n\tsearchParameters: {\r\n\t\tdisjunctiveFacetsRefinements: {\r\n\t\t\trefinement1: ['data1'],\r\n\t\t\trefinement2: ['data2', 'data3']\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n});`\r\nI'm looking for a way to be able to do this with a rangeSlider like so:\r\n\r\n`const search = instantsearch({\r\n\tsearchParameters: {\r\n\t\tdisjunctiveFacetsRefinements: {\r\n\t\t\trefinement1: ['data1'],\r\n\t\t\trefinement2: ['data2', 'data3'],\r\n\t\t\trangeSlider1: {\r\n\t\t\t\tmin: 15,\r\n\t\t\t\tmax: 115\r\n\t\t\t}\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n});`\r\n\r\nThis would be able to maintain the ACTUAL min and max values, but move the selection of the rangeSlider to the above values.\r\n\r\nIf someone knows of a way to do this, it would be greatly appreciated.",
